						               													<description>A shroud of darkness has enveloped the long dormant Obsidian Tower. As it begins to creep unto the surrounding area, skirmishes rife with foul creatures are making a once fertile land desolate and it appears that the kingdom is on the brink of war.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The King has confirmed that this malice is an ancient evil - the Witchlord of Agaroth, also known as the Darkbringer - who has taken refuge within the confines of the sable keep. All willing heroes have been summoned to aid in the battle against this villainy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ancient tales surface of secrets buried with the kings of old; travelers whisper of mystical light sources which can penetrate the depths of any abyss; and that magical items are capable of exiling any evil but are protected within the depths of dark labyrinths.  However, an ominous shadow soars overhead as fire and brimstone erupt upon the horizon &amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Will your party be able to fend off vast insurgencies, make it to the Tower alive, and prevail against this ancient evil?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Adventure awaits only the bravest!  Gather your party of heroes in a quest to save a kingdom under siege. Discover 3 hidden relics and make it to the Obsidian Tower to defeat the Witchlord before his minions can lay waste to all of the land.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Obsidian Tower is an exciting fantasy-based co-operative adventure that supports action for as many as six players, ages 12 and up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
